The paper deals with encoding algorithms for multiplicity codes, which are used in private information retrieval protocols. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions fast multivariate interpolation and evaluation algorithms, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR) due to its application in private information retrieval.
